content:
Run data sync manually 
Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

To run sync: Edit CRM Analytics Dataflows

In data manager, click the Connections tab to display the list of objects enabled for sync grouped by connection.
To show and hide the list of objects, click the connection name.
To run sync for all objects in a connection, click  to the right of the connection name, and select Run Now. The connection is queued to sync.
To run sync for a single remote object, click  to the right of the object name, and select Run Data Sync.

Choose from the following:
Incremental Sync updates only rows that changed since the last sync.
Periodic Full Sync updates rows incrementally and periodically overwrites all rows with records in the Salesforce object.
Full Sync updates all rows with records in the Salesforce object.
Click Save.
Click  again, and select Run Data Sync. Use the Jobs Monitor tab of Data Manager to see the status of your sync.

When reviewing the results of an incremental sync job in Job Manager, the Rows in and Rows out values represent the total number of rows across all syncs.
title: Running Manual Data Sync in CRM Analytics
